meta.name: Svengoolie
meta.description: MeTV is opening up the dungeon door and unleashing... Svengoolie! Svengoolie has been the premiere horror show icon of Chicago, since multiple Emmy award winner Rich Koz became the hand-picked successor to the original Svengoolie back in the late 70s. Since then, generations of viewers have become fans of the monstrous mirth and movies that this video vampire dispenses every week over the airwaves!

videos.title: Duel
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents this thriller starring Dennis Weaver as a driver who somehow ends up with a vengeful trucker after him in Stephen Spielberg's film debut as a director. Follow Weaver along winding roads as the never seen driver torments him. Sven presents us with movie facts and his usual comedy routines throughout the movie.

videos.title: Brides Of Dracula
videos.overview: Svengoolie lets loose with another Hammer Studios Dracula movie featuring the great Christopher Lee in the title Role. Svengoolie gives us facts and trivia throughout along with his offbeat comedy.

videos.title: Sharktopus
videos.overview: House of Svengoolie presents this offbeat film about a genetic mutant. Hang with the Sven Squad as they present facts and comedy with tonight's double feature.

videos.title: Creation Of The Humanoids
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents a film that takes place in the 23rd century, human birth rates has dropped drastically and humans are starting to be replaced by robots. Join Sven as he gives us movie facts along with his comedy bits.

videos.title: The Mummy's Tomb
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts the 3rd in the Mummy series, this is the first time Lon Chaney Jr. appears as the Mummy, Kharis is brought to America 30 years after his discovery to seek revenge on those who defiled his tomb. Sven presents us with movie and actor trivia & tidbits along with his schlock comedy routines.

videos.overview: A millionaire offers $10,000 to five people who agree to be locked in a large, spooky, rented house overnight with him and his wife.

videos.title: Dracula's Daughter
videos.overview: Hungarian countess Marya Zaleska seeks the aid of a noted psychiatrist, hoping to free herself of a mysterious evil influence.

videos.title: House of Dracula
videos.overview: Count Dracula and the Wolf Man seek cures for their afflictions; a hunchbacked woman, a mad scientist and Frankenstein's Monster have their own troubles.

videos.title: Creature from the Black Lagoon
videos.overview: A strange prehistoric beast lurks in the depths of the Amazonian jungle. A group of scientists try to capture the animal and bring it back to civilization for study.

videos.title: Son of Dracula
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts, a woman who lives at a plantation by a Bayou invites the mysterious Count Alucard that she met overseas, to visit her at her home. The Count then makes himself at home while the woman's fiancee and doctor try to discover who the count actually may be.

videos.title: Invisible Man's Revenge
videos.overview: A brilliant scientist discovers how to make things invisible. His formula allows him to exact revenge on his son's murderer, but his revenge comes at a terrible price as the formula begins to consume his mind.

videos.title: Abbott and Costello Meet the Invisible Man
videos.overview: Two detective-school graduates (Bud Abbott, Lou Costello) help a framed boxer who can make himself disappear.

videos.title: The Creature Walks Among Us
videos.overview: A scientist captures the Creature and turns him into an air-breather, only for him to escape and start killing.

videos.title: Bride of Frankenstein
videos.overview: Svengoolie entertains us with his presentation of the sequel to the original Frankenstein. Boris Karloff reprises his role of the monster along with Dwight Frey who comes back as Dr. Pretorius assistant. Sven provides us along the way with his zany humor and tidbits about the movie and it's stars. Fans should remember to duck as the rubber chickens start flying and Sven retreats into his coffin.

Dracula
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents the movie that made Bela Lugosi's career, the 1931 version of Dracula. The evil count comes to England from his castle in Borgo Pass in the Carpathian mountains of Transylvania to seek victims of his blood lust in London. Sven and Doug give us their song, tidbits about behind the scenes of the movie and actors and Sven's usual comic skits. End Credit Qip: "You can not resist Svengoolie' psychic power to compel you to watch again next week!".

Son of Frankenstein
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents the 3rd movie in Universal's classic Frankenstein series. 'Son Of Frankenstein'. Frankenstein's son has a encounter with Ygor, who introduces him to his father's creation after he and his wife arrive to inherit the castle. Sven gives movie facts and trivia. End Credit Quip: 'While Frankenstein is a maker of monsters Svengoolie is just a monster with makeup!'.

videos.title: Revenge of the Creature
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents the 2nd film in the Creature From The Black Lagoon trilogy. The Creature is captured and brought to Marineland in Florida where they try to train him for public display. The creature then escapes and goes on a rampage. Sven gives us behind the scenes movie facts along with a song and his comedic sketches. End Credit Quip: 'Something smells awful fishy around here!'.

videos.title: Bud Abbott Lou Costello Meet Frankenstein
The Ghost of Frankenstein
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts the 4th movie in Universal's classic Frankenstein series. When the towns people blow up the old castle Ygor discovers the Monster in the dried out remains of the tar pit. He then travels to Vasaria to coerce Ludwig Frankenstein, the 2nd son to help bring the creature back to full strength. Svengoolie is on Jury duty so his brother Fraido attempts to take over the show and his fellow puppet Darren makes an appearance. Sven does a Jerry Springer type comedy skit with a cameo by Jerry Springer. Sven does 'Svengoolie On The Road'. End Credit Quip: 'Sven is not a trained ventriloquist but is fully endorsed by the Mortimer Sneed academy!'.

The Mummy (1932)
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts the 1932 Universal release of the Mummy staring Boris Karloff in the title role. A expedition to Egypt encounters more than they bargained for then a strange Egyptian gives them information about a undiscovered princess's lost tomb. End Credit Quip: 'Probably the reason mummys become so restless is because the are wound up tight!'.

videos.title: The Mummy's Hand
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts this followup to Karloff's Mummy, a archeologist gets a lead to a undiscovered tomb and enlists a magician to sponser his expedition. Thinking her father has been conned by the man and his friend, the magicians daughter goes along on the expedition. Sven does his comedic bits, presents trivia about the movie and more. Svengoolie on the road flashback to Chicago Horror Con. End Credit Quip: 'Svengoolie is not a medical professional, but endorses the value of Tana Leaf Tea to boost that killer instinct and feel alive again!'.

videos.title: The Mummy's Ghost
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts the 4th movie in the mummy series. The Mummy returns to find his lost princess causing problems for the towns people. Sven does his comedy schlock, gives movie facts and goes 'On The Road'. After the Mummy's Ghost presentation, Sven hosts a Commando Cody Radar Men From The Moon episode 1 presented in dubbed "Svensurround". End Credit Quip: 'Svengoolie is produced in an environment filled with nits, if you have an aversion to salty silliness you should not have watched!'.

videos.title: It Came from Beneath the Sea
The Two Faces of Dr Jekyll
The Wolf Man
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts the movie that started the werewolf series for Universal Studios and became one of their famous classic monsters. A young man returns home after his brothers death to take over the estate in his brothers place and is bitten while trying to rescue a young lady from an animal attack. Sven gives facts about behind the scenes and presents his usual Shtick.

videos.title: The Mummy's Tomb
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents us with the Mummy's Tomb which picks up 30 years after the Mummy's Hand. A follower of Kharis comes to the States with the mummy and seeks revenge on the original Banner party that discovered the tomb years ago. Sven gives movie and actor trivia. Svengoolie presents a Svensurround episode of Buster Crabbe's Flash Gordon after tonight's movie. End Credit Quip: 'Can you join us in the tomb? We really need a fourth for "Mummy Rummy Night"!'.

videos.title: Dracula's Daughter
videos.overview: Svengoolie airs the sequel to Bela Lugosi's Dracula. The Daughter of Dracula appears on the scene with her servant and battles her vampiric urges. Sven gives facts about the actors and the movie and presents his humor skits along with music with Doug Graves. Sven shows clips from him 'On The Road'. End Credit Quip: 'Dracula's Daughter was great but it can't compare to the last German Film "Nosferatu's Niece!''.

videos.title: Frankenstein
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents the original classic version of 'Frankenstein' that made Boris Karloff into a household name. The scientist creates his creature from body parts then it escapes into the countryside. Svengoolie gives his usual move & actor facts, then goes on the road with interviews with various people. End Credit Quip: 'Creating a monster is definately dangerous, it can leave you tilting at windmills or worse swinging off of one!'.

videos.title: Bride of Frankenstein
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents the 2nd movie in Universals Frankenstein series, 'Bride Of Frankenstein'. Henry Frankenstein is forced to create a mate for his monster by a evil doctor. Sven gives us movie facts, tidbits and trivia as well as a song and his comments throughout the presentation. End Credit Quip: 'After assembling your bride you may want to finish her with paint and custom decals!'.

videos.title: The Creature with the Atom Brain
The Curse of the Mummy's Tomb
The Thing From Another World
videos.overview: Svengoolie brings us this weeks movie entry from his Fortress Of Svenitute, this week features Matheson's The Thing From Another World. A Artic research station discovers a crashed mysterious object, brings a humanoid type being back to their station in a cube of frozen ice. It later thaws with disastrous results. Sven gives info about the movie, actors and does his comedic skits. End Credit Quip: 'We hope you enjoyed this little fling with the Thing!'.

videos.title: The Thing That Couldn't Die
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts a movie about a old chest from the 1500's that is discovered on a California ranch by a young lady who has the power of divination. A crook forces the workman crony to open it, releasing a sinister evil that was cursed and banished almost 500 years in the past. Sven presents his comic skits, goofy songs and the usual movie factoids and trivia. End Credit Quip: 'Thanks for "stick"-ing with us. Now "Head" out and have some fun!'.

videos.title: Abbott and Costello Meet Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde
House of Frankenstein
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts the 6th movie in universal's classic 'Frankenstein' series. Mad Dr. Nieman escapes from prison along with his helper Daniel. He then releases Dracula, encounters the Wolfman and seeks vengeance on the people who put him into jail. Sven gives us facts about the movie and it's actors, does his comedy routines and goes on the road. End Credit Quip: 'If the Frankenstein house is a rockin' don't come a knockin'!'.

videos.title: Son of Dracula
videos.overview: This weeks Svengoolie movie is "Son Of Dracula", with Lon Chaney Jr. in the title role. He uses his powers to seduce a girl who inherits a southern plantation in order to come to the States since he has drained his home country dry. Svengoolie gives us information about the actors and actress's and his comedic skits. End Credit Quip: 'Oh great, there is vampire dust everywhere and my allergies are beginning to kick in!'.

videos.title: Frankenstein Meets the Wolf Man
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts the 5th movie in Universal's classic Frankenstein series. Larry Talbot is exposed to moonlight when grave robbers attempt to steal from his family's tomb releasing him. He seeks to end his curse and encounters a Dr. who agrees to assist. Sven does his schlock, gives movie factoids throughout the presentation. End Credit Quip: 'I told the boys not to rough-house. Now the castle is covered in fur and dead flesh!'.

videos.title: House on Haunted Hill
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts a Vincent Price classic, "The House On Haunted Hill", Price plays a rich business man who offer a group of random people a large sum of money if they will stay the night locked inside of a haunted house. Sven does his skits, funny comments and gives facts about the actors and movie and the house it was filmed in. End Credit Quip: 'You know Svengoolie is much like a ghost, he's not all there and he's used to a lot of booing!'.

videos.overview: Sven hosts this comedy horror where Bud and Lou have a run in with the mad Dr. Jekyll and Bud has belief issues.

videos.title: Dracula's Daughter (1936)
videos.overview: Sven hosts this movie where the story takes place right after Van Helsing staked the infamous vampire in Lugosi's original film, it tells the story of Dracula's daughters attempt to find a cure for her family curse.

videos.title: Attack of the Killer Tomatoes (1978)
videos.overview: Sven hosts the Cult Classic "Attack Of The Killer Tomatoes" where the world is besieged by giant tomatoes that hate humans and the best line is 'Please pass the Ketchup!'.

videos.title: Godzilla: King of the Monsters! (1956)
videos.overview: The Original Americanized version of the great Kaiju's moviie, with the added Raymond Burr footage as the great Godzilla rampages throughout the city of Tokyo.

videos.title: 20 Million Miles to Earth (1957)
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts this movie with Ray Harryhausen stop-motion footage featuring a alien creature that came to Earth.

videos.title: The Curse of the Werewolf (1961)
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts this, the only Werewolf movie made by the Famous Hammer Studios, about a young man cursed with werewolf-ism from birth.

videos.title: Sssssss (1973)
videos.overview: Sven hosts the first movie in this double-feature night, featuring Dirk Benedict going through a experiment that has a strange effect on him, Sven gives the usual movie tidbits.

videos.title: The War of the Gargantuas (1966)
videos.overview: Sven hosts this Toho studio's answer to King Kong times two, movie facts and tidbits abound.

videos.title: The Creature From The Black Lagoon (1954)
The Night Strangler
videos.overview: Svengoolie hosts Darin McGavin in his first appearance as Kolchak. Kolchak encounters a vampire in the Seattle underground in the premier movie for the original series. Sven tells us trivia and facts about the actors and movie.

videos.title: The Ghost And Mr. Chicken
videos.overview: Svengoolie airs one of his most requested movies, Don Knotts as a goofy reporter wanna be who has ghostly encounters that no one believes. Sven gives movie trivia, shows clips from the past 45 years of his show. End Credit Quip: 'If you think you've seen a ghost don't panic, it could just be flickers of light from Sven's jokes burning out!'.

videos.title: What Ever Happened To Baby Jane
videos.overview: House Of Svengoolie airs 'Whatever Happened to Baby Jane' in this double feature night.

videos.title: Them!
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents this James Arness vehicle about a giant ants that run amok both in the desert and then the city. Svengoolie gives movie trivia, actor information and his schlock humor. End Credit Quip: 'Giant ants are scary but giant uncles are even worse, especially at dinner time!'.

videos.title: Arachnophobia
videos.overview: House of Svengoolie's double feature for the night features a giant spider problem.

videos.title: Young Frankenstein
videos.overview: Svengoolie features this beloved Mel Brooks tribute to Frankenstein featuring Gene Wilder as the infamous Dr. Fronkenstien! Sven gives us movie facts and behind the scene and actor info. End Credit Quip: 'Remember, If you're a monster you are only as good as the sum of your parts!'.

videos.title: Frankenstein
videos.overview: House of Svengoolie features the original, Frankenstein, the movie that made Boris Karloff a household name. The ghoulish hosts present Schlock humor, movie tidbits and have a unsuspecting guest at the end of the show.

videos.title: The Fly
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents us with the original 'The Fly' featuring David Hedison of 'Voyage To The Bottom Of The Sea' fame in the lead role as a scientist experimenting with matter transmission and Vincent Price as his brother. Sven gives film trivia and presents his offbeat humor. End Credit Quip: ' I think we all left screaming for help after getting twisted up in some of Sven's half-spun puns!'.

videos.title: Return Of The Fly
videos.overview: House of Svengoolie presents the sequel to the original fly, with Vincent Price reprising his role from the first film.

videos.title: Abbott And Costello Meet Frankenstein
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents 'Abbott And Costello Meet Frankenstein', one of the most fan requested films on the Svengoolie series throughout the years. Join Sven as Bud and Lou encounter the Frankenstein Monster, Bela Lugosi reprising his role as Dracula and Lon Chaney Jr. as the Wolfman. Bud and Lou are accused of stealing a museums missing monsters in this comedic entry. Sven gives us movie facts and actor info. End Credit Quip: 'I hope you enjoyed our reheated casserole with a battered bat, wet werewolf and one well cooked monster!'.

videos.title: The Valley Of Gwangi
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents this Ray Harryhausen stop motion film about a legendary creature that is discovered in a remote valley. Sven gives movie trivia and his offbeat humor routines. End Credit Quip: 'Sven is a lot like Gwangi. He is definately one of a kind and all of his jokes are prehistoric!'.

videos.title: Dracula Has Risen From The Grave
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents a Dracula movie featuring Christopher Lee who reprises his role as the blood hungry Count who becomes upset when he discovers he is barred from his castle. Sven gives us movie and actor facts and his comedy routines.

videos.title: Curse Of The Undead
videos.overview: Svengoolie presents us with what else? a cowboy vampire on the loose. Sven presents movie facts and his comedy schtick. End Credit Quip: 'Now someone please close the barn door before anymore vampires get out!'.

videos.title: Devil Doll
videos.overview: Svengoolie gives us a ventriloquist dummy on the loose this week. Along with movie and actor information and his comedy. End Credit Quip: 'We can not use mind control to get you to watch next week, but only a dummy would miss it!'.

videos.title: A Very Brady Christmas
videos.overview: The Sven Squad give us this Brady bunch special on tonight's House Of Svengoolie special.
